    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName><sic>U S Marshal's</sic> Office</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>St Paul.</placeName>
                <date>Jany 26. 1863</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I have not yet<lb/> recd from you an acknowl-<lb/>edgment of the
                rect of the<lb/> money forwarded to you to pay<lb/> for the books ordered for
                the<lb/> school and also for the<lb/> copies of <persName>Dias'</persName> Letters,
                which<lb/> you sent to me. Should the<lb/> committee call for a rect.<lb/> I would
                like to have one to<lb/> present.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please forward me by mail<lb/> a copy of the “Jews' &amp; the
                Inquisition<lb/> I enclose $1. to pay expenses.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p><sic>have</sic> you copies of the Partical<add>?</add><lb/> works of the
                    “<persName>Misses Moss</persName>”<lb/> which were published some<lb/> time ago.
                I would like to<lb/> have them for my eldest<lb/> girl. Forward them if you<lb/>
                have them and I will<lb/> send the amount required.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My family are well<lb/> &amp; my wife desires to be<lb/>
                remembered.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Yours Respy</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">J N Cardoza</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="Envelope"/>
            <p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Pa</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
